column5: Hey guys, was out with my uncle today from 1-5 and had a great day. Landed maybe 20 perch ranging from 8-12 inches. Was good to see him catch some fish, kept a few also.  We were fisshing small 1" minnows off bottom and sometimes a foot under the ice. Water depth ranged from 6.8-7.2 ft for the most part.  Two biggest was a 11.5 and a 12...still haven't got my 13"+ but I got lot's of time.  Enjoy the pictures  Tightlines everybody, MTBF
Thanks for the reply's guys. Worked hard today with all the running around from line to line haha. Really want to try some new water next weekend...well see   Have a good night fella's.
i have yet to hook into any jumbos this season, hopefully i'll get some soon  nice work
nice perch buddy! We're heading out in the morning - hopefully we get into some fish like that!  Cheers, Ryan
Nice snack!!!! congrats on the jumbo perch.
How did u get a pic of me and dutchy fishing ?
who is the one with the pink?  nice fish Mike.
